def: A supposed rare metallic element, with a characteristicspectrum, found associated with yttrium and other rare metals. Itsindividuality and properties have not yet been determined.
The office or position of a provisor. [R.] J. Webster.
Of or pertaining to bacteriology; as, bacteriological studies.
Continued pain, as distinguished from sudden twinges, orspasmodic pain. "Such an ache in my bones." Shak.
A species of gause, or very silk.The smoke of sulphur . . . is commonly used by women to whitentiffanies. Sir T. Browne.
Of or relating to, or like, cockneys.
The doctrine that matter possesses a species of life andsensation, or that matter and life are inseparable. [R.] Cudworth.
The modification, by inflection or otherwise, which theadjective and adverb undergo to denote degrees of quality orquantity; as, little, less, least, are examples of comparison.
Act or fact of coming or being drawn near or together;establishment or state of cordial relations.
